The Esikhaleni Regional Court in KwaZulu-Natal has convicted and sentenced a 27-year-old man to 25 years&#8217; imprisonment for raping an eight-year-old girl, provincial police said in a statement on Friday. Police spokesperson Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane, said the incident occurred in 2015. On 12 March, 2015, an eight-year-old girl from Mandlakala area was at home with the accused watching television when the accused grabbed and raped her. After finishing, he left the house and went in hiding. Zwane said that the girl reported the matter to her grandmother and a case of rape was opened at Esikhaleni Police Station and the docket transferred to Empangeni Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences unit for further investigation. The suspect was arrested and made several court appearances until he was sentenced.